@node "Installation" "Installation"

 @{b}@{u}Installation@{ub}@{uu}

Please  install  PicView  by  using  the  supplied  installation  script   for
Commodore's  installer  program.  You can choose the directory for the program
and documentation. The locale files will also be installed.
@endnode

@node "Preferences" "Preferences"

 @{b}@{u}The Preferences@{ub}@{uu}

You access the preferences window from the "Project" menu.

 @{u}Screen Mode@{uu}
You can choose your favorite screen mode. You should note that the X/Y  aspect
of the screen should be nearly 1:1, to avoid distortion of the images.
Also you can choose between 16 or 32 colors.

 @{u}File@{uu}
Sets which file should be loaded at program startup. Enter the  directory  and
name of the file here.

 @{u}Picture Viewer@{uu}
If you like another picture viewer better than the built in viewer, you should
activate  the  "External"  option.  Now you can enter the command line for the
viewer into  the  string  gadget.  Use  '%s'  where  the  filename  should  be
substituted.
Example: 'SYS:Utilities/MultiView "%s" SCREEN'
It is recommend to set the '%s' into quotes, because there are  some  problems
otherweise, if there is a blank into the filename

 @{u}Groups@{uu}
This has names of the groups into which pictures can be categorised.
@endnode

@node "History" "History"

 @{b}@{u}History@{ub}@{uu}

V1.0
- first public version

V1.1
- bug while opening the screen on NoAGA-AMIGAs removed
- picture viewer revised, should work now with all commodities

V1.20
- 16 color mode added - makes PicView more useable on all Amigas with ECS
  Chipset

V1.21
- error while saving catalogue picture(s) removed

V1.22
- argument 'CATALOG' added
- error while building catalouge picture(s) removed
  (forgotten to wait for the blitter)


Some thinks for the future:
- ARexx port
- multiselection
- large sort and selection functions
- 256 color mode
- support of animations
- Xpk support
- 32 groups
- comment for every picture
- creation and presentation of picture shows

@endnode
